{"name": "low-index", "metadata": {"name": "low-index", "version": "1.2", "classifiers": ["Development Status :: 5 - Production/Stable", "Intended Audience :: Science/Research", "License :: OSI Approved :: GNU General Public License v2 or later (GPLv2+)", "Operating System :: OS Independent", "Programming Language :: C++", "Programming Language :: Python", "Topic :: Scientific/Engineering :: Mathematics"], "home_page": "https://github.com/3-manifolds/low_index", "license": "GPLv2+", "documentation_url": null, "dependencies": [], "summary": "Enumerates low index subgroups of a finitely presented group", "upload_time": 1684616952}, "documentation": ["# Low Index Subgroups\n\nThe low_index project provides a Python module which implements a variant\nof Charles Sims' Low Index Subgroups algorithm for enumerating all of\nthe conjugacy classes of subgroups of a finitely presented group with\nfinite index less than a given bound.\n\nThe package is available on pypi, so the simplest way to install it for\nPython versions 3.6 - 3.11 is to use pip:\n\n```bash\npip3 install low-index\n```\n\nHere is a sample computation:\n\n```python\n>>> from low_index import *\n>>>  # Conjugacy classes of subgroups of F_3 with index at most 4:\n>>> reps = permutation_reps(rank = 3, short_relators = [], long_relators = [], max_degree = 4)\n>>> len(reps)\n653\n>>> from snappy import *\n>>> G = Manifold('K11n34').fundamental_group(); G\nGenerators:\n   a,b,c\nRelators:\n   aaBcbbcAc\n   aacAbCBBaCAAbbcBc\n>>> # Degree at most 7 covers of the exterior of the Conway knot:\n>>> reps = permutation_reps(G.num_generators(), G.relators()[:1], G.relators()[1:], 7)\n>>> len(reps)\n52\n>>> reps[25]\n[[1, 0, 3, 2, 5, 6, 4], [1, 4, 0, 6, 2, 5, 3], [3, 0, 2, 6, 4, 1, 5]]\n```\n\n# Credits\n\nPrimarily developed by [Marc Culler](https://marc-culler.info),\n[Nathan Dunfield](http://dunfield.info), and [Matthias Goerner](http://www.unhyperbolic.org/)\n\n# License\n\nCopyright 2022 by Marc Culler, Nathan Dunfield, Matthias Goerner\nand others.\n\nThis code is released under the [GNU General Public License, version 2](http://www.gnu.org/licenses/gpl-2.0.txt) or (at your option) any\nlater version as published by the Free Software Foundation.\n"], "modules": [{"name": "setup", "documentation": [], "functions": [], "variables": [{"name": "setup.sources", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "setup.extra_compile_args", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "setup.extra_compile_args", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "setup.ext_modules", "type": null, "documentation": []}], "classes": [{"name": "setup.Clean", "bases": ["Command"], "methods": [{"name": "setup.Clean.initialize_options", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "setup.Clean.finalize_options", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "setup.Clean.run", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}], "class_variables": [{"name": "setup.Clean.user_options", "type": null, "documentation": []}], "instance_variables": [], "inner_classes": [], "documentation": []}], "exports": []}, {"name": "python_src.benchmark", "documentation": [], "functions": [{"name": "python_src.benchmark.run_example", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "ex", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "num_threads", "type": null, "default": "..."}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "python_src.benchmark.run_example_low_level", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "ex", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "python_src.benchmark.run", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "ex", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "num_threads", "type": null, "default": "..."}], "returns": null, "documentat